urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ii.294#and bought what he liked, provided that he increased the yearly business
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ii.295#of his department in a certain proportion, settled beforehand; and it
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ii.296#was on this proportion that his commission was based. In short, his
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ii.297#position at The Ladies' Paradise, like that of all the managers, was
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ii.298#that of a special tradesman, in a grouping of various businesses, a sort
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ii.299#of vast trading city.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ii.300#“So,” resumed he, “it's decided we mark it five francs twelve sous? It's
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ii.301#barely the cost price, you know.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ii.302#“Yes, yes, five francs twelve sous,” said Mouret, quickly; “and if I
