urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.806#francs to Bourras. Do you speak to him first about it. Tell him he's
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.807#cutting his own throat. Perhaps he'll listen to you, as he has a liking
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.808#for you, and you'll be doing him a real service.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.809#“Very well!” said Denise, smiling also, “I will deliver your message,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.810#but I am afraid I shall not succeed.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.811#And a fresh silence ensued, neither of them having anything more to say.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.812#He attempted to talk of her uncle Baudu; but had to give it up on seeing
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.813#the young girl's uneasiness. However, they continued to walk side by
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.814#side, and at last found themselves near the Rue de Rivoli, in a path
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.815#where it was still light. On coming out of the darkness of the trees it
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.816#was like a sudden awakening. He understood that he could not detain her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.817#any longer.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.818#“Good night, mademoiselle.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.819#“Good night, sir.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.820#But he did not go away. On raising his eyes he perceived in front of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.821#him, at the corner of the Rue d'Alger, the lighted windows at Madame
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.822#Desforges's, whither he was bound. And looking at Denise, whom he could
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.823#now see, in the pale twilight, she appeared to him very puny beside
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.824#Henriette. Why was it she touched his heart in this way? It was a stupid
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.825#caprice.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.826#“This little man is getting tired,” resumed he, just for something to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.827#say. “Remember, mind, that our house is always open to you; you've only
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.828#to knock, and I'll give you every compensation possible. Good night,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.829#mademoiselle.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.830#“Good night, sir,”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.831#When Mouret quitted her, Denise went back under the chestnut-trees,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.832#in the black shadow. For a long time she walked on without any object,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.833#between the enormous trunks, her face burning, her head in a whirl of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.834#confused ideas. Pépé still had hold of her hand, stretching out his
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.835#short legs to keep pace with her. She had forgotten him. At last he
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.836#said:
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.837#“You go too quick, little mother.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.838#At this she sat down on a bench; and as he was tired, the child went to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.839#sleep on her lap. She held him there, nestling to her virgin bosom,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.840#her eyes lost far away in the darkness. When, an hour later on, they
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.841#returned slowly to the Rue de la Michodière, she had regained her usual
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.842#quiet, sensible expression.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.843#“Hell and thunder!” shouted Bourras, when he saw her coming, “the blow
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.844#is struck. That rascal of a Mouret has just bought my house.” He was
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.845#half mad, and was striking himself in the middle of the shop with such
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.846#outrageous gestures that he almost threatened to break the windows. “Ah!
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.847#the scoundrel! It's the fruiterer who's written to tell me this. And
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.848#how much do you think he has got for the house? One hundred and fifty
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.849#thousand francs, four times its value! There's another thief, if you
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.850#like! Just fancy, he has taken advantage of my embellishments, making
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.851#capital out of the fact that the house has been done up. How much longer
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.852#are they going to make a fool of me?”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.853#The thought that his money spent on paint and white-wash had brought
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.854#the fruiterer a profit exasperated him. And now Mouret would be his
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.855#landlord; he would have to pay him! It was beneath this detested
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.856#competitor's roof, that he must live in future! Such a thought raised
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.857#his fury to the highest possible pitch.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.858#“Ah! I could hear them digging a hole through the wall. At this moment,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.859#they are here eating out of my very plate, so to say!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.860#And the shop shook under his heavy fist which he banged on the counter;
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.861#he made the umbrellas and the parasols dance again. Denise, bewildered,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.862#could not get in a word. She stood there, motionless, waiting for the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.863#end of his tirade; whilst Pépé, very tired, had fallen asleep on a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.864#chair. At last, when Bourras became a little calmer, she resolved to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.865#deliver Mouret's message. No doubt the old man was irritated, but the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.866#excess even of his anger, the blind alley in which he found himself,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.867#might determine an abrupt acceptance.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.868#“I've just met some one,” she commenced. “Yes, a person from The
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.869#Paradise, very well informed. It appears that they are going to offer
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.870#you eighty thousand francs to-morrow.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.871#“Eighty thousand francs!” interrupted he, in a terrible voice; “eighty
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.872#thousand francs! Not for a million now!” She tried to reason with him.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.873#But at that moment the shop door opened, and she suddenly drew back,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.874#pale and silent. It was her uncle Baudu, with his yellow face and aged
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.875#look. Bourras seized his neighbour by the button-hole, and roared out
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.876#in his face without allowing him to say a word, as if goaded on by his
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.877#presence:
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.878#“What do you think they have the cheek to offer me? Eighty thousand
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.879#francs! They've got so far, the brigands! they think I'm going to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.880#sell myself like a prostitute. Ah! they've bought the house, and think
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.881#they've now got me. Well! it's all over, they sha'n't have it! I might
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.882#have given way, perhaps; but now it belongs to them, let them try and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.883#take it!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.884#“So the news is true?” said Baudu in his slow voice. “I had heard of it,
