urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.895#he still replied no. In nine years' time he hoped to be dead, so as
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.896#not to see it “You hear, Monsieur Baudu,” resumed he, “your niece is on
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.897#their side, it's her they have employed to corrupt me. She's with the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.898#brigands, my word of honour!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.899#Baudu, who up to then had appeared not to notice Denise, now raised his
