urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.903#“I know it,” replied he in a half-whisper, and he continued to look at
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.904#her.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.905#Denise, affected almost to tears, thought him greatly changed by
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.906#trouble. Perhaps he was stricken with remorse for not having assisted
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.907#her during the time of misery she had just passed through. Then the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.908#sight of Pépé sleeping on the chair, amidst the noise of the discussion,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.909#seemed to suddenly inspire him with compassion.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.910#“Denise,” said he simply, “come to-morrow and have dinner with us and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:vii.911#bring the little one. My wife and Geneviève asked me to invite you if I
