urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.652#Robineau's place. He even showed himself so intolerable, after the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.653#promises of good-fellowship, with which he had formerly warmed his
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.654#colleagues, that the latter were now secretly supporting Favier against
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.655#him.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.656#“Now, then, no back answers,” replied Hutin sharply. “Monsieur
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.657#Bouthemont wishes you to show some light designs in silks.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.658#In the middle of the department, an exhibition of summer silks lighted
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.659#up the hall with an aurora-like brilliancy, like the rising of a star,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.660#in the most delicate tints possible: pale rose, tender yellow, limpid
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.661#blue, the entire gamut of Iris. There were silks of a cloudy fineness,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.662#surahs lighter than the down falling from the trees, satined pekins soft
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.663#and supple as a Chinese virgin's skin. There were, moreover, Japanese
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.664#pongees, Indian tussores and corahs, without counting the light French
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.665#silks, the thousand stripes, the small checks, the flowered patterns,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.666#all the most fanciful designs, which made one think of ladies in
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.667#furbelows, walking about, in the sweet May mornings, under the immense
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.668#trees of some park.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.669#“I'll take this, the Louis XIV. with figured roses,” said Madame
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.670#Desforges at last.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.671#And whilst Favier was measuring it, she made a last attempt with
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.672#Bouthemont, who had remained near her.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.673#“I'm going up to the ready-made department to see if there are any
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.674#travelling cloaks. Is she fair, the young lady you were talking about?”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.675#The manager, who felt rather anxious on finding her so persistent,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.676#merely smiled. But, just at that moment, Denise went by. She had just
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.677#passed on to Liénard, who had charge of the merinoes, Madame Boutarel,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.678#that provincial lady who came up to Paris twice a year, to scatter all
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.679#over The Ladies' Paradise the money she scraped together out of her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.680#housekeeping. And as Favier was about to take up Madame Desforges's
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.681#silk, Hutin, thinking to annoy him, interfered.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.682#“It's quite unnecessary, Mademoiselle Denise will have the kindness to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.683#conduct this lady.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.684#Denise, quite confused, at once took charge of the parcel and the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.685#debit-note. She could never meet this young man face to face without
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.686#experiencing a feeling of shame, as if he reminded her of a former
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.687#fault; and yet she had only sinned in her dreams.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.688#“But, tell me,” said Madame Desforges, in a low tone, to Bouthemont,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.689#“isn't it this awkward girl? He has taken her back, then? But it is she,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.690#the heroine of the adventure!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.691#“Perhaps,” replied the head of department, still smiling, and fully
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.692#decided not to tell the truth.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.693#Madame Desforges then slowly ascended the staircase, preceded by Denise;
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.694#but she had to stop every two or three steps to avoid being carried away
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.695#by the descending crowd. In the living vibration of the whole
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.696#building, the iron supports seemed to stagger beneath the weight, as if
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.697#continually trembling from the breath of the crowd On each stair was
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.698#a dummy, strongly fixed, displaying some garment: a costume, cloak,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.699#or dressing-gown; and it was like a double row of soldiers for some
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.700#triumphal march-past, with the little wooden arm like the handle of a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.701#poniard, stuck into the red swan-skin, which gave a bloody appearance to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.702#the stump of a neck crowning the whole.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.703#Madame Desforges was at last reaching the first storey, when a still
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.704#greater surging of the crowd forced her to stop once more. She had now,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.705#beneath her, the departments on the ground-floor, with the press of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.706#customers she had just passed through. It was a new spectacle, a sea
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.707#of heads fore-shortened, concealing the bodices, swarming with a busy
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.708#agitation. The white price tickets now appeared but so many thin lines,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.709#the promontory of flannels cut through the gallery like a narrow
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.710#wall; whilst the carpets and the embroidered silks which decked the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.711#balustrades hung at her feet like processional banners suspended from
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.712#the gallery of a church. In the distance, she could perceive the angles
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.713#of the lateral galleries, as from the top of a steeple one perceives
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.714#the corners of the neighbouring streets, with the black spots of the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.715#passers-by moving about. But what surprised her above all, in the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.716#fatigue of her eyes blinded by the brilliant pell mell of colours, was,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.717#when she lowered her lids, to feel the crowe more than its dull noise
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.718#like the rising tide, and the human warmth that it exhaled. A fine dust
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.719#rose from the floor, laden with the odour of woman, the odour of her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.720#linen and her bust, of her skirts and her hair, an invading, penetrating
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.721#odour, which seemed to be the incense of this temple raised for the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.722#worship of her body.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.723#Meanwhile Mouret, still standing up before the reading-room with De
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.724#Vallagnosc, was inhaling this odour, intoxicating himself with it, and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.725#repeating: “They are quite at home. I know some who spend the whole day
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.726#here, eating cakes and writing their letters. There's only one thing
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.727#more to do, and that is, to find them beds.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.728#This joke made Paul smile, he who, in the _ennui_ of his pessimism,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.729#continued to think the crowd stupid in thus running after a lot of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.730#gew-gaws. Whenever he came to give his old comrade a look up, he went
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.731#away almost vexed to see him so full of life amidst his people of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.732#coquettes. Would not one of them, with shallow brain and empty heart,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.733#teach him one day the stupidity and uselessness of existence? That very
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.734#day Octave seemed to lose some of his admirable equilibrium; he who
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.735#generally inspired his customers with a fever, with the tranquil grace
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.736#of an operator, was as though seized by the passion with which the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.737#establishment was gradually burning. Since he had caught sight of Denise
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.738#and Madame Desforges coming up the grand staircase, he had been talking
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.739#louder, gesticulating against his will; and, whilst affecting not to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.740#turn his face towards them, he became more and more animated as he felt
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.741#them drawing nearer. His face got redder, his eyes had a little of that
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.742#rapture with which the eyes of his customers ultimately vacillated.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.743#“You must be robbed fearfully,” murmured De Vallagnosc, who thought the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.744#crowd looked very criminal.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.745#Mouret threw his arms out “My dear fellow, it's beyond all imagination.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.746#And, nervously, delighted at having something to talk about, he gave a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.747#number of details, related cases, and classified the subjects. In the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.748#first place, there were the professional thieves; these women did the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.749#least harm of all, for the police knew every one of them. Then came the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.750#kleptomaniacs, who stole from a perverse desire, a new sort of nervous
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.751#affection which a mad doctor had classed, proving the results of the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.752#temptation provided by the big shops. In the last place must be counted
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.753#the women in an interesting condition, whose robberies were of a special
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.754#order. For instance, at the house of one of them, the superintendent of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.755#police had found two hundred and forty-eight pairs of pink gloves stolen
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.756#from every shop in Paris.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.757#“That's what makes the women have such funny eyes here, then,” murmured
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.758#De Vallagnosc; “I've been watching them with their greedy, shameful
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.759#looks, like mad creatures. A fine school for honesty!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.760#“Hang it!” replied Mouret, “though we make them quite at home, we can't
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.761#let them take away the goods under their mantles. And sometimes they are
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.762#very respectable people. Last week we had the sister of a chemist, and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.763#the wife of a councillor. We try and settle these matters.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.764#He stopped to point out Jouve, the inspector, who was just then looking
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.765#sharp after a woman in the family way, down below at the ribbon counter.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.766#This woman, whose enormous belly suffered a great deal from the pushing
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.767#of the crowd, was accompanied by a friend, whose mission appeared to be
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.768#to defend her against the heavy shocks, and each time she stopped in a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.769#department, Jouve did not take his eyes off her, whilst her friend near
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.770#her ransacked the card-board boxes at her ease.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.771#“Oh! he'll catch her!” resumed Mouret; “he knows all their tricks.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.772#But his voice trembled, he laughed in an awkward manner. Denise and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.773#Henriette, whom he had ceased to watch, were at last passing behind him,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.774#after having had a great deal of trouble to get out of the crowd. He
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.775#turned round suddenly, and bowed to his customer with the discreet air
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.776#of a friend who does not wish to compromise a woman by stopping her in
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.777#the middle of a crowd of people. But the latter, on the alert, had at
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.778#once perceived the look with which he had first enveloped Denise. It
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.779#must be this girl, this was the rival she had had the curiosity to come
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.780#and see.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.781#In the ready-made department, the young ladies were losing their heads.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.782#Two of them had fallen ill, and Madame Frédéric, the second-hand, had
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.783#quietly given notice the previous day, and gone to the cashier's office
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.784#to take her money, leaving The Ladies' Paradise all in a minute, as
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.785#The Ladies' Paradise itself discharged its employees. Ever since the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.786#morning, in spite of the feverish rush of business, every one had
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.787#been talking of this adventure. Clara, maintained in the department by
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.788#Mouret's caprice, thought it grand. Marguerite related how exasperated
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.789#Bourdoncle was; whilst Madame Aurélie, greatly vexed, declared that
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.790#Madame Frédéric ought at least to have informed her, for such hypocrisy
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.791#had never before been heard of.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.792#Although the latter had never confided in any one, she was suspected of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.793#having given up drapery business to marry the proprietor of some of the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.794#baths in the neighbourhood of the Halles.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.795#“It's a travelling cloak that madame desires, I believe?” asked Denise
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.796#of Madame Desforges, after having offered her a chair.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.797#“Yes,” replied the latter, curtly, decided on being rude.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.798#The new decorations of the department were of a rich severity: high
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.799#carved oak cupboards, mirrors filling the whole space of the panels,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.800#and a red Wilton carpet, which stifled the continued movement of the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.801#customers. Whilst Denise was gone for the cloaks, Madame Desforges,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.802#who was looking round, perceived herself in a glass; and she continued
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.803#contemplating herself. She must be getting old to be cast aside for
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.804#the first-comer. The glass reflected the entire department with its
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.805#commotion, but she only beheld her own pale face; she did not hear
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.806#Clara behind her relating to Marguerite instances of Madame Frederic's
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.807#mysterious ways, the manner in which she went out of her way night and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.808#morning to go through the Passage Choiseul, in order to make believe
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.809#that she perhaps lived over the water.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.810#“Here are our latest designs,” said Denise. “We have them in several
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.811#colours.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.812#She laid out four or five cloaks. Madame Desforges looked at them with
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.813#a scornful air, and became harsher at each fresh one she examined. Why
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.814#those frillings which made the garment look so scanty? and the other
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.815#one, square across the shoulders, one would have thought it had been
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.816#cut out with a hatchet. Though it was for travelling she could not dress
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.817#like a sentry-box.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.818#“Show me something else, mademoiselle.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.819#Denise unfolded and folded the garments without the slightest sign of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.820#ill temper. And it was just this calm, serene patience which exasperated
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.821#Madame Desforges still further. Her looks continually returned to the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.822#glass in front of her. Now that she saw herself there, close to Denise,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.823#she made a comparison. Was it possible that he should prefer this
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.824#insignificant creature to herself? She now remembered that this was the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.825#girl she had formerly seen making her début with such a silly figure,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.826#awkward as a peasant girl just arrived from her village. No doubt she
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.827#looked better now, stiff and correct in her silk dress. But how puny,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.828#how common-place!
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.829#“I will show you some other models, madame,” said Denise, quietly.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.830#When she returned, the scene began again. Then it was the cloth that was
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.831#heavy and no good whatever. Madame Desforges turned round, raised her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.832#voice, endeavouring to attract Madame Aurélie's attention, in the hope
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.833#of getting the young girl a scolding. But Denise, since her return, had
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.834#gradually conquered the department, and now felt quite at home in
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.835#it; the first-hand had even recognised in her some rare and valuable
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.836#qualities as a saleswoman--an obstinate sweetness, a smiling conviction.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.837#Therefore Madame Aurélie simply shrugged her shoulders, taking care not
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.838#to interfere.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.839#“Would you kindly tell me the kind of garment you require, madame?”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.840# asked Denise, once more, with her polite persistence, which nothing
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.841#could discourage.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.842#“But you've got nothing!” exclaimed Madame Desforges.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.843#She stopped, surprised to feel a hand laid on her shoulder. It was
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.844#Madame Marty, carried right through the establishment by her fever
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.845#for spending. Her purchases had increased to such an extent, since the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.846#cravats, the embroidered gloves, and the red parasol, that the last
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.847#salesman had just decided to place the whole on a chair, for it would
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.848#have broken his arm; and he walked in front of her, drawing the chair
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.849#along, on which was heaped up a pile of petticoats, napkins, curtains, a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.850#lamp, and three straw hats.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.851#“Ah!” said she, “you are buying a travelling cloak.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.852#“Oh! dear, no,” replied Madame Desforges; “they are frightful.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.853#But Madame Marty had just noticed a striped cloak which she rather
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.854#liked. Her daughter Valentine was already examining it. So Denise called
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.855#Marguerite to clear the article out of the department, it being a model
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.856#of the previous year, and the latter, at a glance from her comrade,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.857#presented it as an exceptional bargain. When she had sworn that they had
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.858#lowered the price twice, that from a hundred and fifty francs, they had
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.859#reduced it to a hundred and thirty, and that it was now at a hundred and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.860#ten, Madame Marty could not withstand the temptation of its cheapness.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.861#She bought it, and the salesman who accompanied her left the chair and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.862#the parcel, with the debit-notes attached to the goods.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.863#Meanwhile, behind the ladies' backs, and amidst the jostlings of the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.864#sale, the gossip of the department about Madame Frédéric still went on.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.865#“Really! she had some one?” asked a little saleswoman, fresh in the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.866#department.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.867#“The bath-man of course!” replied Clara. “Mustn't trust those sly, quiet
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.868#widows.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.869#Then while Marguerite was debiting, Madam Marty turned her head and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.870#desired Clara by a slight movement of the eyebrows, she whispered to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.871#Madame Desforges: “Monsieur Mouret's caprice, you know!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.872#The other, surprised, looked at Clara; then, turning her eyes towards
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.873#Denise, replied: “But it isn't the tall one; the little one!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.874#And as Madame Marty could not be sure which, Madame Desforges resumed
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.875#aloud, with the scorn of a lady for chambermaids: “Perhaps the tall one
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.876#and the little one; all those who like!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.877#Denise had heard everything. She turned pale, and raised her big, pure
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.878#eyes on this lady who was thus wounding her, and whom she did not know.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.879#No doubt it was the lady of whom they had spoken to her, the lady whom
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.880#the governor saw outside. In the look that was exchanged between them,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.881#Denise displayed such a melancholy dignity, such a frank innocence, that
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.882#Henriette felt quite awkward.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.883#“As you have nothing presentable to show me here, conduct me to the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.884#dress and costume department,” said she, abruptly.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.885#“I'll go with you as well,” exclaimed Madame Marty, “I wanted to see a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.886#costume for Valentine.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.887#Marguerite took the chair by its back, and dragged it along on its hind
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.888#feet, that were getting worn by this species of cartage. Denise only
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.889#carried a few yards of silk, bought by Madame Desforges. It was quite
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.890#a journey, now that the robes and costumes were on the second floor, at
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.891#the other end of the establishment.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.892#And the long journey commenced along the crowded galleries. Marguerite
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.893#walked in front, drawing the chair along, like a little carriage,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.894#slowly opening herself a passage. As soon as she reached the under-linen
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.895#department, Madame Desforges began to complain: wasn't it ridiculous, a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.896#shop where one was obliged to walk a couple of leagues to find the least
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.897#thing! Madame Marty also said she was tired to death, yet she did not
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.898#the less enjoy this fatigue, this slow exhaustion of her strength,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.899#amidst the inexhaustible treasures displayed on every side. Mouret's
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.900#idea, full of genius, seized upon her, stopping her at each department.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.901#She made a first halt before the trousseaux, tempted by some chemises
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.902#that Pauline sold her; and Marguerite found herself relieved from the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.903#burden of the chair, which Pauline had to take, with the debit-notes.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.904#Madame Desforges could have gone on her road, and thus have liberated
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.905#Denise quicker, but she seemed happy to feel her behind her, motionless
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.906#and patient, whilst she was lingering there, advising her friend. In
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.907#the baby-linen department the ladies went into ecstasies, without buying
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.908#anything. Then Madame Marty's weakness commenced anew; she succumbed
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.909#successively before a black silk corset, a pair of fur cuffs, sold at
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.910#a reduction on account of the lateness of the season, and some Russian
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.911#lace much in vogue at that time for trimming table-linen. All these
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.912#things were heaped up on the chair, the parcels still increased, making
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.913#the chair creak; and the salesmen who succeeded each other, found it
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.914#more and more difficult to drag along as the load became heavier.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.915#“This way, madame,” said Denise without a murmur, after each halt.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.916#“But it's absurd!” exclaimed Madame Desforges. “We shall never get
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.917#there. Why not have put the dresses and costumes near the ready-made
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.918#department? It is a jumble!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.919#Madame Marty, whose eyes were sparkling, intoxicated by this succession
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.920#of riches dancing before her, repeated in a half whisper:
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.921#“Oh, dear! What will my husband say? You are right, there is no order in
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.922#this place. You lose yourself, and commit all sorts of follies.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.923#On the great central landing, the chair, could barely pass. Mouret had
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.924#just blocked the space with a lot of fancy goods, drinking-cups mounted
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.925#on gilded zinc, trashy dressing-cases and liqueur stands, being of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.926#opinion that the crowd was not sufficiently great, and that circulation
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.927#was too easy. He had authorised one of his shopmen to exhibit there on
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.928#a small table Chinese and Japanese curiosities, knick-knacks at a low
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.929#price, which the customers eagerly snatched up. It was an unexpected
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.930#success, and he already thought of extending this business. Whilst
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.931#two messengers carried the chair up to the second storey, Madame Marty
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.932#bought six ivory studs, some silk mice, and an enamelled match-box.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.933#On the second floor the journey was continued. Denise, who had been
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.934#showing customers about in this way since the morning, was dropping with
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.935#fatigue; but she still continued correct, amiable, and polite. She had
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.936#to wait for the ladies again in the furnishing materials department,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.937#where a ravishing cretonne had tempted Madame Marty. Then, in the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.938#furniture department, it was a work-table that took her fancy. Her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.939#hands trembled, she jokingly entreated Madame Desforges to prevent her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.940#spending any more, when a meeting with Madame Guibal furnished her with
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.941#an excuse. It was in the carpet department, where the latter had gone to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.942#return a lot of Oriental door-curtains bought by her five days before.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.943#And she was standing, talking to the salesman, a brawny fellow, who,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.944#with his sinewy arms handled from morning to night loads heavy enough to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.945#kill a bullock. Naturally he was quite astounded at this “return,”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.946# which deprived him of his commission. He did his best to embarrass his
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.947#customer, suspecting some queer adventure, no doubt a ball given with
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.948#these curtains, bought at The Ladies' Paradise, and then returned, to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.949#avoid hiring at an upholsterer's: he knew this was frequently done by
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.950#the needy portion of society. In short, she must have some reason for
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.951#returning them; if she did not like the designs or the colours, he
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.952#would show her others, he had a most complete assortment. To all these
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.953#insinuations Madame Guibal replied in the quietest, most unconcerned
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.954#manner possible, with a queenly assurance that the curtains did not suit
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.955#her, without deigning to add any explanation. She refused to look at any
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.956#others, and he was obliged to give way, for the salesmen had orders to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.957#take back the goods, even if they saw they had been used.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.958#As the three ladies went off together, and Madame Marty referred with
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.959#remorse to the work-table for which she had no earthly need, Madame
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.960#Guibal said in her calm voice: “Well! you can return it. You saw it was
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.961#quite easy. Let them send it home. You can put it in your drawing-room,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.962#keep it for a time, then if you don't like it, return it!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.963#“Ah! that's a good idea!” exclaimed Madame Marty. “If my husband makes
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.964#too much fuss, I'll send everything back.” This was for her the supreme
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.965#excuse, she calculated no longer, but went on buying, with the secret
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.966#wish to keep everything, for she was not a woman to give anything back.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.967#At last they arrived in the dress and costume department. But as Denise
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.968#was about to deliver to another young lady the silk bought by Madame
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.969#Desforges, the latter seemed to change her mind, and declared that she
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.970#would decidedly take one of the travelling cloaks, the light grey one
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.971#with the hood; and Denise had to wait complacently to bring her back
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.972#to the ready-made department. The young girl felt herself being treated
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.973#like a servant by this imperious, whimsical customer; but she had
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.974#sworn to herself to do her duty, and retained her calm attitude,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.975#notwithstanding the rising of her heart and the shock to her pride.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.976#Madame Desforges bought nothing in the dress and costume department.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.977#“Oh! mamma,” said Valentine, “if that little costume should fit me!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.978#In a low tone, Madame Guibal was explaining her tactics to Madame Marty.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.979#When she saw a dress she liked in a shop, she had it sent home, took
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.980#the pattern of it, and then sent it back. And Madame Marty bought
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.981#the costume for her daughter remarking: “A good idea! You are very
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.982#practical, my dear madame.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.983#They had been obliged to abandon the chair. It had been left in
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.984#distress, in the furniture department, with the work-table. The weight
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.985#was too much, the hind legs threatened to break off; and it was arranged
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.986#that all the purchases should be centralised at one pay-desk, and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.987#from there sent down to the delivery department. The ladies, still
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.988#accompanied by Denise, then began wandering all about the establishment,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.989#making a second appearance in nearly every department. They seemed to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.990#take up all the space on the stairs and in the galleries. Every
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.991#moment some fresh meeting brought them to a standstill. Thus, near the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.992#reading-room, they once more came across Madame Bourdelais and her three
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.993#children. The youngsters were loaded with parcels: Madeline had a dress
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.994#for herself, Edmond was carrying a collection of little shoes, whilst
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.995#the youngest, Lucien, was wearing a new cap.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.996#“You as well!” said Madame Desforges, laughingly, to her old
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.997#school-fellow.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.998#“Pray, don't speak of it!” cried out Madame Bourdelais. “I'm furious.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.999#They get hold of us by the little ones now! You know what a little I
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1000#spend on myself! But how can you expect me to resist the voices of these
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1001#young children, who want everything? I had come just to show them round,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1002#and here am I plundering the whole establishment!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1003#Mouret, who happened to be there still, with De Vallagnosc and Monsieur
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1004#de Boves, was listening to her with a smile. She observed it, and gaily
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1005#complained, with a certain amount of real irritation, of these traps
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1006#laid for a mother's tenderness; the idea that she had just yielded to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1007#the fevers of advertising raised her indignation, and he, still smiling,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1008#bowed, fully enjoying this triumph. Monsieur de Boves had manoeuvred so
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1009#as to get near Madame Guibal, whom he ultimately followed, trying for
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1010#the second time to lose De Vallagnosc; but the latter, tired of the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1011#crush, hastened to rejoin him. Denise was again brought to a standstill,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1012#obliged to wait for the ladies. She turned her back, and Mouret himself
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1013#affected not to see her. Madame Desforges, with the delicate scent of a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1014#jealous woman, had no further doubt. Whilst he was complimenting her and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1015#walking beside her, like a gallant host, she was deep in thought, asking
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1016#herself how she could convince him of his treason.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1017#Meanwhile Monsieur de Boves and De Vallagnosc, who were on in front with
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1018#Madame Guibal, had reached the lace department, a luxurious room, near
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1019#the ready-made department, surrounded with stocks of carved oak drawers,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1020#which were constantly being opened and shut. Around the columns, covered
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1021#with red velvet, were spirals of white lace; and from one end of the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1022#department to the other, hung lengths of Maltese; whilst on the counters
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1023#there were quantities of large cards, wound round with Valenciennes,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1024#Malines, and hand-made point At the further end two ladies were seated
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1025#before a mauve silk skirt, on which Deloche was placing pieces of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1026#Chantilly, the ladies looking on silently, without making up their
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1027#minds.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1028#“Hallo!” said De Vallagnosc, quite surprised, “you said Madame de Boves
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1029#was unwell. But there she is standing over there near that counter, with
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1030#Mademoiselle Blanche.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1031#The count could not help starting back, and casting a side glance at
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1032#Madame Guibal.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1033#“Dear me! so she is,” said he.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1034#It was very warm in this room. The customers, half stifled, had pale
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1035#faces with flaming eyes. It seemed as if all the seductions of the shop
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1036#had converged into this supreme temptation, that it was the secluded
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1037#alcove where the customers were doomed to fall, the corner of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1038#perdition where the strongest must succumb. Hands were plunged into the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1039#overflowing heaps, retaining an intoxicating trembling from the contact.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1040#“I fancy those ladies are ruining you,” resumed De Vallagnosc, amused at
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1041#the meeting.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1042#Monsieur de Boves assumed the look of a husband perfectly sure of his
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1043#wife's discretion, from the simple fact that he did not give her a sou
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1044#to spend. The latter, after having wandered through all the departments
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1045#with her daughter, without buying anything, had just stranded in the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1046#lace department in a rage of unsated desire. Half dead with fatigue, she
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1047#was leaning up against the counter. She dived about in a heap of lace,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1048#her hands became soft, a warmth penetrated as far as her shoulders. Then
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1049#suddenly, just as her daughter turned her head and the salesman went
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1050#away, she was thinking of slipping a piece of point d'Alençon under her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1051#mantle. But she shuddered, and dropped it, on hearing De Vallagnosc's
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1052#voice saying gaily:
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1053#“Ah! we've caught you, madame.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1054#For several seconds she stood there speechless and pale. Then she
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1055#explained that, feeling much better, she thought she would take a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1056#stroll. And on noticing that her husband was with Madame Guibal, she
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1057#quite recovered herself, and looked at them with such a dignified air
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1058#that the other lady felt obliged to say:
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1059#“I was with Madame Desforges when these gentlemen met us.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1060#The other ladies came up just at that moment, accompanied by Mouret,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1061#who again detained them to point out Jouve the inspector, who was still
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1062#following the woman in the family way and her lady friend. It was very
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1063#curious, they could not form any idea of the number of thieves that were
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1064#arrested in the lace department. Madame de Boves, who was listening,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1065#fancied herself between two gendarmes, with her forty-six years, her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1066#luxury, and her husband's fine position; but yet she felt no remorse,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1067#thinking she ought to have slipped the lace up her sleeve. Jouve,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1068#however, had just decided to lay hold of the woman in the family way,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1069#despairing of catching her in the act, but fully suspecting her of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1070#having filled her pockets, with a sleight of hand which had escaped him.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1071#But when he had taken her aside and searched her, he was wild to find
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1072#nothing on her--not a cravat, not a button. Her friend had disappeared.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1073#All at once he understood: the woman in the family way was only there as
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1074#a blind; it was the friend who did the trick.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1075#This affair amused the ladies. Mouret, rather vexed, merely said: “Old
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1076#Jouve has been floored this time. He'll have his revenge.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1077#“Oh!” replied De Vallognosc, “I don't think he's equal to it. Besides,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1078#why do you display such a quantity of goods? It serves you right, if you
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1079#are robbed. You ought not to tempt these poor, defenceless women so.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1080#This was the last word, which sounded like the sharp note of the day,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1081#in the growing fever of the establishment. The ladies then separated,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1082#crossing the crowded departments for the last time. It was four o'clock,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1083#the rays of the setting sun were darting through the large windows in
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1084#the front, lighting up crossways the glazed roofs of the halls, and in
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1085#this red, fiery light sprung up, like a golden vapour, the thick dust
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1086#raised by the circulation of the crowd. A broad ray ran along the grand
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1087#central gallery, showing up on a flaming ground the staircases, the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1088#flying bridges, all the network of suspended iron. The mosaics and the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1089#terra-cotta of the friezes sparkled, the green andred paint were lighted
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1090#up by the fire of the masses of gold scattered everywhere. It was like a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1091#red-hot furnace, in which the displays were now burning, the palaces of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1092#gloves and cravats, the clusters of ribbons and lace, the lofty piles of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1093#linen and calico, the diapered parterres in which flourished the light
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1094#silks and foulards. The exhibition of parasols, with their shield-like
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1095#roundness, threw out a sort of metallic reflection. In the distance were
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1096#a lot of lost counters, sparkling, swarming with a moving crowd, ablaze
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1097#with sunshine.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1098#And at this last moment, amidst this over-warmed air, the women reigned
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1099#supreme. They had taken the whole place by storm, camping there as in
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1100#a conquered country, like an invading horde installed amongst the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1101#overhauling of the goods. The salesmen, deafened, knocked up, were
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1102#now nothing but their slaves, of whom they disposed with a sovereign's
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1103#tyranny. Fat women elbowed their way through the crowd. The thinnest
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1104#ones took up a lot of space, and became quite arrogant. They were all
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1105#there, with heads high and abrupt gestures, quite at home, without the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1106#slightest politeness one for the other, using the house as much as they
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1107#could, even carrying away the dust from the walls. Madame Bourdelais,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1108#desirous of making up for her expenditure, had again taken her children
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1109#to the refreshment bar; the crowd was now pushing about there in a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1110#furious way, even the mothers were gorging themselves with Malaga; they
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1111#had drunk since the opening eighty quarts of syrup and seventy bottles
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1112#of wine. After having bought her travelling cloak, Madame Desforges
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1113#had managed to secure some pictures at the pay-desk; and she went away
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1114#scheming to get Denise into her house, where she could humiliate
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1115#her before Mouret himself, so as to see their faces and arrive at a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1116#conclusion. Whilst Monsieur de Boves succeeded in losing himself in the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1117#crowd and disappearing with Madame Guibal, Madame de Boves, followed by
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1118#Blanche and De Vallagnosc, had had the fancy to ask for a red air-ball,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1119#although she had bought nothing. It was always something, she would not
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1120#go away empty-handed, she would make a friend of her doorkeeper's little
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1121#girl with it. At the distributing counter they were just commencing the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1122#fortieth thousand: forty thousand red air-balls which had taken flight
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1123#in the warm air of the shop, quite a cloud of red air-balls which were
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1124#now floating from one end of Paris to the other, bearing upwards to the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1125#sky the name of The Ladies' Paradise!
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1126#Five o'clock struck. Of all the ladies, Madame Marty and her daughter
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1127#were the only ones to remain, in the final crisis of the sale. She could
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1128#not tear herself away, although ready to drop with fatigue, retained by
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1129#an attraction so strong that she was continually retracing her steps,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1130#though wanting nothing, wandering about the departments out of a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1131#curiosity that knew no bounds. It was the moment in which the crowd,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1132#goaded on by the advertisements, completely lost itself; the sixty
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1133#thousand francs paid to the newspapers, the ten thousand bills posted on
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1134#the walls, the two hundred thousand catalogues distributed all over the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1135#world, after having emptied their purses, left in the women's minds the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1136#shock of their intoxication; and the customers still remained, shaken by
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1137#Mouret's other inventions, the reduction of prices, the “returns,” the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1138#endless gallantries. Madame Marty lingered before the various stalls,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1139#amidst the hoarse cries of the salesmen, the chinking of the gold at the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1140#pay-desks, and the rolling of the parcels down into the basement; she
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1141#again traversed the ground floor, the linen, the silk, the glove,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1142#and the woollen departments; then she went upstairs again, abandoning
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1143#herself to the metallic vibrations of the suspended staircases and the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1144#flying-bridges, returning to the ready-made, the under-linen, and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1145#the lace departments; she even ascended to the second floor, into the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1146#heights of the bedding and furniture department; and everywhere the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1147#employees, Hutin and Favier, Mignot and Liénard, Deloche, Pauline and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1148#Denise, nearly dead with fatigue, were making a last effort, snatching
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1149#victories from the expiring fever of the customers. This fever had
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1150#gradually increased since the morning, like the intoxication arising
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1151#from the tumbling of the stuffs. The crowd shone forth under the fiery
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1152#glare of the five o'clock sun. Madame Marty's face was now animated and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1153#nervous, like that of an infant after drinking pure wine. Arrived with
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1154#clear eyes and fresh skin from the cold of the street, she had slowly
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1155#burnt her sight and complexion, at the spectacle of this luxury, of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1156#these violent colours, the continued gallop of which irritated her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1157#passion. When she at last went away, after saying she would pay at home,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1158#terrified by the amount of her bill, her features were drawn up, her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1159#eyes were like those of a sick person. She was obliged to fight her way
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1160#through the crowd at the door, where the people were almost killing each
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1161#other, amidst the struggle for the bargains. Then, when she got into
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1162#the street, and found her daughter, whom she had lost for a moment, the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1163#fresh air made her shiver, she stood there frightened in the disorder of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1164#this neurosis of the immense establishments.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1165#In the evening, as Denise was returning from dinner, a messenger called
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1166#her: “You are wanted at the director's office, mademoiselle.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1167#She had forgotten the order Mouret had given her in the morning, to go
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1168#to his office after the sale. He was standing waiting for her. On going
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1169#in she did not close the door, which remained, wide open.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1170#“We are very pleased with you, mademoiselle,” said he, “and we have
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1171#thought of proving our satisfaction. You know in what a shameful manner
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1172#Madame Frédéric has left us. From to-morrow you will take her place as
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1173#second-hand.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1174#Denise listened to him immovable with surprise. She murmured in a
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1175#trembling voice: “But, sir, there are saleswomen in the department who
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1176#are much my seniors.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1177#“What does that matter?” resumed he. “You are the most capable, the most
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1178#trustworthy. I choose you; it's quite natural. Are you not satisfied?”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1179#She blushed, feeling a delicious happiness and embarrassment, in
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1180#which her first fright vanished. Why had she at once thought of the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1181#suppositions with which this unhoped for favour would be received? And
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1182#she stood filled with her confusion, notwithstanding her sudden burst of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1183#gratitude. He was looking at her with a smile, in her simple silk dress,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1184#without a single piece of jewellery, nothing but the luxury of her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1185#royal, blonde head of hair. She had become more refined, her skin was
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1186#whiter, her manner delicate and grave. Her former puny insignificance
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1187#was developing into a charm of a penetrating discretion.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1188#“You are very kind, sir,” she stammered. “I don't know how to tell
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1189#you----”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1190#But she was cut short by the appearance of Lhomme in the doorway. In his
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1191#hand he was holding a large leather bag, and with his mutilated arm he
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1192#was pressing an enormous notecase to his chest; whilst, behind him, his
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1193#son Albert was carrying a load of bags, which were weighing him down.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1194#“Five hundred and eighty-seven thousand two hundred and ten francs
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1195#thirty centimes!” cried out the cashier, whose flabby, used-up face
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1196#seemed to be lighted up with a ray of sunshine, in the reflection of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1197#such a sum.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1198#It was the day's receipts, the highest The Ladies' Paradise had ever
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1199#done. In the distance, in the depths of the shop that Lhomme had just
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1200#passed through slowly, with the heavy gait of an overloaded beast of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1201#burden, one could hear the uproar, the ripple of surprise and joy, left
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1202#by this colossal sum which passed.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1203#“But it's superb!” said Mouret, enchanted. “My good Lhomme, put it down
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1204#there, and take a rest, for you look quite done up. I'll have this money
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1205#taken to the central cashier's office. Yes, yes, put it all on my table,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1206#I want to see the heap.”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1207#He was full of a childish gaiety. The cashier and his son laid down
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1208#their burdens. The leather bag gave out a clear, golden ring, two of the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1209#other bags bursting let out a stream of silver and copper, whilst from
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1210#the note-case peeped forth corners of bank notes. One end of the large
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1211#table was entirely covered; it was like the tumbling of a fortune picked
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1212#up in ten hours.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1213#When Lhomme and Albert had retired, mopping their faces, Mouret remained
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1214#for a moment motionless, lost, his eyes fixed on the money. Then,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1215#raising his head, he perceived Denise, who had drawn back. He began to
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1216#smile again, forced her to come forward, and finished by saying he
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1217#would give her all she could take in her hand; and there was a sort of
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1218#love-bargain beneath his playfulness.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1219#“Look! out of the bag. I bet it would be less than a thousand francs,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1220#your hand is so small!”
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1221#But she drew back again. He loved her, then? Suddenly she understood,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1222#she felt the growing flame of desire with which he had enveloped her
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1223#since, her return to the shop. What overcame her more than anything else
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1224#was to feel her heart beating violently. Why did he wound her with all
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1225#this money, when she was overflowing with gratitude, and he could have
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1226#done anything with her by a friendly word? He was coming closer to her,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1227#continuing to joke, when, to his great annoyance, Bourdoncle appeared,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1228#under the pretence of informing him of the number of entries--the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1229#enormous number of seventy thousand customers had entered The Ladies'
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1230#Paradise that day. And she hastened away, after having again thanked
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:ix.1231#him.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.1#CHAPTER X.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.2#The first Sunday in August every one was busy with the stock-taking,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.3#which had to be finished by the evening. Early in the morning all the
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.4#employees were at their posts, as on a week-day, and the work commenced
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.5#with closed doors, in the immense establishment, entirely free from
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.6#customers.
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.7#Denise, however, had not come down with the other young ladies at eight
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.8#o'clock. Confined to her room for the last five days by a sprained
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.9#ankle, caused when going up stairs to the work-rooms, she was going on
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.10#much better; but, sure of Madame Aurélie's indulgence, she did not hurry
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.11#down, and sat putting her boots on with difficulty, resolved, however,
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.12#to show herself in the department. The young ladies' bed-rooms now
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.13#occupied the entire fifth storey of the new buildings, along the Rue
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.14#Monsigny; there were sixty of them, on either side of a corridor, and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.15#they were much more comfortable than formerly, although still
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.16#furnished with the iron bedstead, large wardrobe, and little mahogany
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.17#toilet-table. The private life of the saleswomen became more refined and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:x.18#elegant there, they displayed a taste for scented soap and fine linen,
