urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:xiv.249#to the left, in the Monsigny Gallery, jutted out the white promontories
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:xiv.250#of cotton and calico, the white rocks formed of sheets, napkins, and
urn:cts:fuTexts:zola.paradise.novoa:xiv.251#handkerchiefs; whilst to the right, in the Michodière Gallery, occupied
